==English==
===Verb===
'''to gabble'''
# to talk fast, idly, foolishly, or without meaning
#*'''1883:''' Robert Louis Stevenson, ''Treasure Island'' – ...I could hear nothing but a low '''gabbling'''; but at last the voices began to grow higher, and I could pick up a word or two...

